Section 1:
1 L.D. 110
2 Date: (Filing No. H- )
3 HEALTH AND HUMAN SERVICES
5 STATE OF MAINE
6 HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
7 132ND LEGISLATURE
8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 75, L.D. 110, “An Act to Require
10 Reporting on the Expenditure of Opioid Settlement Funds by Certain Municipalities and
11 County Governments”
12 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the enacting clause and inserting the
13 following:
14 'Sec. 1. 5 MRSA §203-D is enacted to read:
15 §203-D. Reporting on funds received by direct share subdivisions pursuant to court
16 settlement of opioid crisis litigation
17 A direct share subdivision that receives funds pursuant to settlements described in
18 section II.A of the Memoranda of Understanding shall submit a report to the Attorney
19 General by January 15, 2026, and annually thereafter, detailing the amount of such funds
20 received pursuant to section II.C.2 of each Memoranda of Understanding and expended in
21 the prior calendar year, including a description of each such expenditure. The Attorney
22 General shall compile these reports and submit them by February 15, 2026 and annually
23 thereafter to the joint standing committee of the Legislature having jurisdiction over health
24 and human services matters.
25 As used in this section, "Memoranda of Understanding" has the same meaning as in
26 section 203-C, subsection 1, paragraph C and "direct share subdivision" means a
27 municipality or county that is a subdivision identified in Exhibit 3 of the Memoranda of
28 Understanding.'
29 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
30 number to read consecutively.
31 SUMMARY
3322 This amendment replaces the bill. The amendment clarifies the application of the
3333 reporting requirements for direct share subdivisions. It adds a requirement that the
3344 Attorney General compile the reports submitted by direct share subdivisions and submit
Page 1 - 132LR0033(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 75, L.D. 110
315 them by February 15, 2026 and annually thereafter to the joint standing committee of the
326 Legislature having jurisdiction over health and human services matters.
337 FISCAL NOTE REQUIRED
348 (See attached)
Page 2 - 132LR0033(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT
